question: I am almost 39 weeks, ftm. I'm so frustrated! My cervix is halfway ripened, I haven't dilated, cervix still closed. My baby boy is estimated to be 9.5 lbs at 40 weeks.  I have gestational diabetes, so my Dr says it won't be safe to deliver naturally with gs if baby is more than 9 lbs because of broader shoulders. Although he had a nurse make an appointment for me at the hospital to be induced on my due date.  If my body doesn't react to the meds he will perform a c-section.  I really want to have my baby naturally! Who has tried using evening primrose oil, walking, and using a breast pump to help with the labor process? What worked for you?
title: 38 weeks, 5 days
